        <h2>What is Rio Miner?</h2>
        <p>
          Rio Miner is a <strong>real crypto mining app</strong> for Android devices. It connects to mining pools
          you configure, uses your device's CPU/GPU to mine, and displays live metrics like hashrate,
          shares, and uptime in a clean, miner-style dashboard.
        </p>
        <p>
          Mining on mobile hardware is generally <strong>not efficient</strong> and may not be profitable.
          Rio Miner is intended for people who understand the tradeoffs and want to experiment, learn,
          or monitor small-scale mining from their phone.
        </p>
        <div>
          <span class="tag">Real Mining</span>
          <span class="tag">Advanced Users</span>
          <span class="tag">No Profit Guarantee</span>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Key Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Connect to mining pools you configure (pool URL, wallet address, worker name).</li>
          <li>Live stats: hashrate, accepted/rejected shares, session uptime, and temperature.</li>
          <li>Wallet balance display for your mining wallet (if supported by your setup).</li>
          <li>Miner-console style log output for every share and connection event.</li>
          <li>Optional ads to support development (no pay-to-mine or deposits).</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
